    <statement><p>The diagram shows a simplified circuit in which two independent components <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> are connected in parallel.</p><p></p><p style="text-align: center;"><img src="figure1.svg" alt="" width="172" height="73" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"></p><p></p><p>The circuit functions if either or both of the components are operational. It is known that if <m>A</m> is the event 'component <m>a</m> is operating' and <m>B</m> is the event 'component <m>b</m> is operating' then <m>\text{P}(A)=0.{95}</m>, <m>\text{P}(B)=0.{97}</m> and <m>\text{P}(A\cap B)=0.{94}</m>.&nbsp; Find the probability that the circuit is functioning.</p><p><fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/> </p></statement>
    <solution><p>The probability that the circuit is functioning is <m>\text{P}(A\cup B)</m>. In words: either <m>a</m> or <m>b</m> or</p><p>both must be functioning if the circuit is to function. Using the keypoint:</p><p><me>\begin{eqnarray*}\text{P}(A\cup B)&amp;=&amp;\text{P}(A)+\text{P}(B)-\text{P}(A\cap B)\\ &amp;=&amp;0.{95}+0.{97}-0.{94}=0.{98} \end{eqnarray*}</me></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>0.98</m></p></answer>
